  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue1" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Hey, you! Yeah, you, the new recruit in the armor.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue2" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>You're not gonna stand there all day, are you?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue3" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Prove to me you can stand on your own two feet.
Grab your character and move it around the screen.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue4" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Not bad, you're not completely rusty!</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue5" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Now hover over your character
to discover the menu.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue6" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>See your name at the top? That's you.
Right now you're level 0, but that's about to change.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue7" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The blue bar under your name is your experience.
It fills up every time you click on your character.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue8" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The number below shows how much XP you've earned this level,
and how much you need to reach the next one.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue9" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The three lines below are your stats:
HP, DMG and AGI.
We'll get back to those.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue10" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The FIGHT button at the bottom is where it all begins.
That's the one that starts battles.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue11" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>And at the very bottom, your shortcuts:
Friends, Leaderboard, Inventory, Shop, and Settings.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue12" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Here you can find your friends and track their progress.
You can also fight a friend's ghost by clicking the Fight button.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue13" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Compare yourself to the best players in the world.
Climb the rankings by stacking up XP.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue14" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>This is where you pick your skin.
Customize the look of your character.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue15" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>This is where you choose your combat mode.
Dungeon, Ranked, and Event.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue16" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Fight players from around the world in real time.
Climb the leaderboard to make a name for yourself.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue17" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Here you can tweak the game to your liking.
Sound, language, notifications... it's all here.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue18" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Perfect, you know the ropes now.
Click anywhere to earn XP.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue19" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Not bad at all!
Now you'll need to build some muscle before stepping into the arena.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue20" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Keep clicking until you reach level 1!
Every click brings you closer to the goal.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue21" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Nice work! You've reached level 1!
It's time to choose your skills.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue22" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>HP: More health points.
The more you have, the more hits you can take.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue23" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>DMG: More damage.
Hit harder, kill faster.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue24" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>AGI: More evasion.
The higher it is, the sooner you strike in combat.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue25" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Your turn.
Choose wisely, every point counts!</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue26" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>There you go, you've gotten stronger!
Every point invested makes a difference in battle.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue27" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>To wrap up the training, you can jump into a quick Ranked match.
But you don't have to, it's your call.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tuto_Dialogue28" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>That's everything I had to teach you.
Good luck, warrior. The rest is up to you.</value>
  </data>
